# SQL migrations for the per-user storage file.
#
# Implementation phase will land here as `NNN_<slug>.sql` files, applied in
# lexical order against an open SQLite + SQLCipher connection. The first
# migration creates the schema documented in `../spec/storage-format.md`.
#
# Conventions:
#
#   001_initial_schema.sql        — _meta, event_types, channels, ...,
#                                   audit_log, peer_sync, all initial indexes
#   002_<additive>.sql            — additive columns / tables only; never
#                                   drops or renames
#
# Migrations record their version in `_meta.format_version`. The schema
# loader checks this on file open and applies missing steps; no whole-file
# rewrites.
#
# This .gitkeep keeps the directory in version control until real migrations
# land; the build doesn't depend on it.
